definitions.definition: An accumulation ; an increase ; a gradual development .
examples: Snow buildup on roads makes for hazardous driving.
There was a buildup of pressure in the boiler.

definitions.definition: The construction of a composite core to repair a damaged tooth .

main_definition: An accumulation ; an increase ; a gradual development .
secondary_definitions: ( dentistry ) The construction of a composite core to repair a damaged tooth .
